    <bioghist>Oral history project conducted by Gwendolyn Hall under the auspices of the Michigan Historical Collections.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Tapes and transcripts of oral interviews with persons concerned with the problem of drug addiction and the methadone treatment of drug rehabilitation, including George P. Agnello, James Brickley, Earl Chestang, George Crockett, Chuck Gordon, Elder Hammett, H. Richard Henderson, Ezekiel Kious, Carl Levin, Paul Lowinger, William Lucas, Richard Martin, Betty Pecsenye (no transcript), Edward Pierce, Thomas Stacknic, John B. Swainson, and one anonymous interview; also collected material. Tapes are available only for Agnello, Brickley, Crockett, Hammett, Henderson, Levin, Lowinger, Pecsenye, Pierce, Stacknic, Swainson, and anonymous.</scopecontent>
